<subSubSection id="E65CECAFAEF504FFC92EB8F510ED579B" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="notes">
<paragraph id="82755E96CD23D8096ADD3BFF5D81B71A" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="831CA19F5C5FF41D3AEA1CFB18B06D1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Just like 
<taxonomicName id="4269163EA38782E7A398641BA7B5E833" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Asplenium alatulum" order="Filicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alatulum">
<emphasis id="A97576FF73564A4E6FBF9A0A7F2537B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Asplenium alatulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a comprehensive taxonomic study of 
<taxonomicName id="32C94E2DA311C57DEED61AB7E84240D6" class="Filicopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. subcrenatum" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="subcrenatum">
<emphasis id="CE6738EEC987EFD042287610716001F6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A. subcrenatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was scarce after this species was described. 
<bibRefCitation id="467A36850E2F1DCCCE45447593FFB078" author="Lin, YX" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="2 - 3). Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="267 - 316" refId="B12" refString="Lin, YX, Viane, R, 2013. Aspleniaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Hong, DY, Eds., Flora of China (Vol. 2-3). Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis: 267 - 316" title="Aspleniaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of China (Vol." year="2013">Lin and Viane (2013)</bibRefCitation>
treated it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="6B73BDE945AF6F973584DFB03D94233D" class="Filicopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. wrightii" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="wrightii">
<emphasis id="1BBD62F344271251272082B8A43D8EAE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A. wrightii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based only on macromorphological data. Both our molecular data (
<bibRefCitation id="74E99D0981583343271C180E2A2D6107" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12384" author="Xu, KW" journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="22 - 71" refId="B24" refString="Xu, KW, Zhang, L, Rothfels, CJ, Smith, AR, Viane, R, Lorence, D, Wood, KR, Chen, CW, Knapp, R, Zhou, L, Lu, NT, Zhou, X-M, Wei, H-J, Fan, Q, Chen, S-F, Cicuzza, D, Gao, X-F, Liao, W-B, Zhang, L-B, 2020. A global plastid phylogeny of the fern genus Asplenium (Aspleniaceae). Cladistics 36 (1): 22 - 71, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12384" title="A global plastid phylogeny of the fern genus Asplenium (Aspleniaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/cla.12384" volume="36" year="2020">Xu et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
) and micromorphological data in this study (Figs 
<figureCitation id="348BD92483A4EB39AB45A2585770F8F1" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Scanning electron micrographs of spore and stomata of A. alatulum, A. subcrenatum and A. wrightii A-F A. wrightii G-I A. subcrenatum J-L A. alatulum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.172.62511.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/509066" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FDC715D139CF1DDB416F03595835C6C3" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Scales of A. alatulum, A. subcrenatum and A. wrightii. A, D, G A. wrightii B, E, H A. subcrenatum C, F, I A. alatulum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.172.62511.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/509067" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2</figureCitation>
) support the distinction of 
<taxonomicName id="CF0917B10334C55A96AE0818ED9BCBCC" class="Filicopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. subcrenatum" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="subcrenatum">
<emphasis id="2C89DF69113BC24E90949AFCE0E3FF6C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A. subcrenatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85A88E0C4B286CAE782E9F370DD8E304" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName id="D9781B8B4E6B52D18EF8F0208F9564CB" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Asplenium subcrenatum" order="Filicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subcrenatum">
<emphasis id="9A9F46BF9349FCA12ACC0A0BE8324F01" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Asplenium subcrenatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different from 
<taxonomicName id="8F7D10FE68339D388D6AD2858D1351DD" class="Filicopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. wrightii" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="wrightii">
<emphasis id="2FAC296638295CFE364FB45A33E20339" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A. wrightii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having its stipe and rachis covered with reddish-brown scales (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="965BAA017A69E8100BC2CF265E008B15" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Scales of A. alatulum, A. subcrenatum and A. wrightii. A, D, G A. wrightii B, E, H A. subcrenatum C, F, I A. alatulum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.172.62511.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/509067" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2B, E, H</figureCitation>
) (vs. brown to dark brown scales, Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8D3736A8272C53B0E03E2EFC5E34FC27" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Scales of A. alatulum, A. subcrenatum and A. wrightii. A, D, G A. wrightii B, E, H A. subcrenatum C, F, I A. alatulum." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.172.62511.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/509067" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2A, D, G</figureCitation>
), scale margins nearly entire (vs. glandular margins or long-fibrillose) and pinna margins almost entire to crenate-sinuate (vs. serrate to coarsely dentate). Meanwhile, the perispores of 
<taxonomicName id="6CDDEA244D3387B651248627871B9FBF" class="Filicopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. subcrenatum" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="subcrenatum">
<emphasis id="6306059BF5554F7CBF7776C5BD731EA1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A. subcrenatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are different from those of 
<taxonomicName id="FBA70165AC2F2D537E38DDB03846301F" class="Filicopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. wrightii" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="wrightii">
<emphasis id="0E968E5D4C590F12ACD974C0D26C5745" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A. wrightii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The folds of 
<taxonomicName id="D867399CFF8F67BDA97B30294A7E4B92" class="Filicopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. subcrenatum" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="subcrenatum">
<emphasis id="290E9BEBCB5AE18B0E9F9C171A720DE2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A. subcrenatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are cristato-alate and areolofenestrate and the margins of the folds are echinulate, while the folds of 
<taxonomicName id="ACA371312E26F405C6F9D2AE1F754D54" class="Filicopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. wrightii" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="wrightii">
<emphasis id="B521F2B13C5D21C6A5153775DF5D0111" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A. wrightii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are cristato-alate and imperforate and the margins of the folds are echinulate or approximately laevigate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="092EC62C05560691EACE78E60DE865FE" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Geographically, 
<taxonomicName id="440BD4C5D0FF43BED85CF7ABC6AC083C" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Asplenium subcrenatum" order="Filicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subcrenatum">
<emphasis id="2C0550381D7D9D87DE415B82B28A70FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Asplenium subcrenatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was only known from the type locality Malipo County and Yanshan County, southern Yunnan, China (
<bibRefCitation id="C6CAAF005692B08431F6A73D87B094AC" author="Wu, SH" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="6). Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="3 - 127" refId="B23" refString="Wu, SH, 1999. Aspleniaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Ed., Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae (Vol. 6). Science Press, Beijing: 3 - 127" title="Aspleniaceae." volumeTitle="Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae (Vol." year="1999">Wu 1999</bibRefCitation>
). Our study, based on specimen investigations and the field survey, shows that this species is mainly distributed in limestone areas of south-western China and northern Vietnam, while 
<taxonomicName id="686111709E6AA4F392F0BBED59BA635D" class="Filicopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="A." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="A. wrightii" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Pteridophyta" rank="species" species="wrightii">
<emphasis id="8D7E2480BBBF2E330007998604A6D5BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A. wrightii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in acidic soils in southern China and Japan and it might occur in Korea.
</paragraph>
